main event: A blinking red and white light was observed in the sky near Orogrande, New Mexico.
interesting points: The light varied in intensity from very dim to very bright.
The light moved vertically at a high rate of speed.
Several aircraft were in the area at the time, but the object did not appear consistent with their conditions.
The observation lasted for approximately 15 minutes.
The observer was an electronic technician at White Sands Missile Range, whose reliability estimate was considered good.
sighted object: a blinking red and white light in the sky
witnesses: an electronic technician at White Sands Missile Range
